precision(x) returns the decimal precision of a real or complex kind.

default real examples:
a(i) = 0  precision(a(i)) = 6
a(i) = 1  precision(a(i)) = 6
a(i) = -1  precision(a(i)) = 6
a(i) = 100  precision(a(i)) = 6

real kind examples:
precision(1.0)   = 6
precision(1.0_4) = 6
precision(1.0_8) = 15

complex examples:
precision((1.0, 2.0))     = 6
precision((1.0_4, 2.0_4)) = 6
precision((1.0_8, 2.0_8)) = 15
